dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived 2-foot Contours for Jefferson County, WI 2011
dc_description_s: This data represents LiDAR-derived 2-foot contours for Jefferson County, Wisconsin in 2011. A contour is a line through all contiguous points of equal elevation value. Contours are vector features used to represent the elevation of a landscape in a relatively familiar way. They are typically used for basemaps and general topographic representation. This data is available in both SHP and DWG formats.
uw_supplemental_s: This data is also available as a series of tiles to enable downloads of smaller, more specific areas within the county. To access the tiled data, please visit: https://www.sco.wisc.edu/scoapps/lidar/tile-search/?layer=jefferson
